# Backend Website App Guide

The [website](mdc:server/apps/website) app in the backend contains:

- [views.py](mdc:server/apps/website/views.py): Defines view functions or classes for handling web requests.
- [models.py](mdc:server/apps/website/models.py): Contains database models for the website app.
- [admin.py](mdc:server/apps/website/admin.py): Registers models for the Django admin interface.
- [apps.py](mdc:server/apps/website/apps.py): App configuration.
- [tests.py](mdc:server/apps/website/tests.py): Test cases for the website app.
- [migrations](mdc:server/apps/website/migrations): Database migration files.
- [templates](mdc:server/apps/website/templates): HTML templates for rendering views.
- [__init__.py](mdc:server/apps/website/__init__.py): Marks the directory as a Python package.

Refer to the [backend structure guide](mdc:backend.mdc) for more details on backend organization.
